 Port Elizabeth - A 25-year-old Kwanoxolo man was shot in his buttocks after three unknown males entered his house in Joza Street Street during the early hours of Saturday morning. "It is alleged that at about 04:40, the complainant was asleep when he was awakened by the three men in his room," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "One suspect pointed a firearm at him. They demanded money and his cellphone. . "A small amount of cash and his cellphone was taken." She said that the complainant grappled with the suspect with the firearm and he was shot in his buttocks. "The suspects entered the house by breaking a bedroom window. They left through the same window." A 9mm pistol suspected to that of the suspect’s was found behind a couch. "The serial number is filed off. A case of house robbery is under investigation. The complainant was taken to hospital for treatment." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 